      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEVINGTON (6) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 2 length win at Shepparton in a handy 25.07. Has a tricky draw to overcome but has a good record over this journey. Hard to fault the current string of winning form and can continue his winning ways. PERCY (3) is unbeaten over this distance in three starts. Was out of placings last time (30.06) at Sandown in a Special conditions G3, finishing eighth and beaten 9 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. SHE'S PRIMED (7) shapes nicely here coming off a head turning 23.85 win at Bendigo over 425m. In form and looks a leading player again. ASTON HERCULES (2) drops in trip and should be in the mix.",
